The evidence with the title 'Nuclear power and renewables don't have to be enemies. New York ... ' says Aug 2, 2016  ... Consider , if you will, two basic facts about clean energy in the United States. Nuclear power is the country 's largest source of carbon-free energy, supplying about 19 percent of our electricity , but it's barely growing. Wind and solar are smaller , at about 8 percent, but they're growing much more rapidly. 
